caption: We stumbled upon this place, 3 of us. I saw that a window was open so we waited for service but no one came. There were patrons seated at tables inside. I poked my head in to see what the scene was and a bartender scolded me for poking my head in. He was very condescending and literally said "who does that?" I said what, poke my head in?? He didn't like that. He said "you're done" and refused to serve us. Very strange, very rude. That was my experience at this place. Good luck. I'll never go here again.

Hipsters everywhere but there was plenty of room for me and bae to find a seat and enjoy dinner.

I love their fried chicken.

With a heavy heart and after hundreds of review, for the first time giving a place a 1 star review.  Terrible service provided when my friend and I went for a quick bite last night. Looking at the reviews, I am not surprised that others have had a the same experience, and treated in the same way by the same woman - as described "slightly chunky woman with heavy mascara and brown/blonde hair". So 10pm ish we get to commodore – super excited to try their fried chicken+burger. The lady tells us to take the free table. We ask for the menu - she brings it - then  - we dont see her for some time - and after getting her - we tell her we want to order. She mentions to go to the bar to order – we do so. We had to negotiate with people ordering drinks - to get through to bar tender to order food. We made the HUGE mistake or not asking for water then - and had to go back to the bar. After about 20 minutes, not sure if food would come to our table or the bar – we ask about it, and she says “relax, you will get your food” – which sounded very rude since it was a relatively simple question. At the 20 minute point (we were quite relaxed) - our fries come– upon which we ask the logical question – when we would get our food. This hit a nerve .. and she says “do you need exact time in minutes… you know this is not a fast food joint …”…. This did piss me off – and I asked her why she was being unnecessarily rude … she goes “I’ve already wasted a lot of time explaining how this place works” …. I told her “hmmm you work here – so that’s your job” – which seems to have offended her even more and clarifies she is a foodrunnner not a waiter. After being aggravated - she has the audacity to tell a paying customer “you know I can kick you out of the restaurant”…. Not trying to lose my cool and quite perplexed at the interaction, I stay at my table for couple more minutes. It was quite surreal - and we werent sure how to react... At the 30 minute mark our burger and fried chicken were here - which were literally "thrown / slided" to us......but our appetite was gone. Feeling insulted, embarrassed and confused at this interaction - I went back to the bar – gave the food back and told the bar tender that the waiter was extremely rude, and preferred that I leave – so I will do so without eating (that too after waiting for almost 40 minutes). The bartender was apologetic saying that he will waive the bill or give me a free drink… but I wanted to pay (and so I did) and didn’t want any freebee, since I wanted to leave the impression that we were not even). I write this review being more sad than angry - such a popular establishment being run by untrained and unprofessional staff and sad that a place like this is in Brooklyn. I am not sad however to have not tried their fried chicken - since I can assure you that’s its not worth the terrible service we got.

Went in assuming this is a fried chicken place/restaurant/hole in the wall. But to my surprise this was a dive bar - with ability order food from the bar. I'd have gone to another dive bar - if i had wanted to go to a dive bar. The service was very dissapointing - rude staff - slow food. Overall - go there if you are interested to go to a dive bar - dont go there expecting to sit somewhere and eat fried chicken. (And sweet chic is better)

the food is amazing. the staff is awesome. some of the patrons are way too cool but that is what happens when a place is that good.

This is an old school, hipstery bar that serves food.  Pretty good food! They are known for the fried chicken and we went for brunch,  had the fried chicken biscuit. It was legit! Walked in and got a seat since the sign said to seat yourselves. After waiting for someone to come after 10 minutes, we asked another customer and they said to order at the bar.
